<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4140] Use of non-thread-safe function gmtime()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4140</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Method &lt;b&gt;THttpServer::getTimeRFC1123()&lt;/b&gt; (in lib/cpp/src/thr8ft/transport/THttpServer.cpp) uses gmtime().&lt;br/&gt;
This function is documented to be not thread-safe (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Broken_002ddown-Time.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Broken_002ddown-Time.html&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, we should use gmtime_r().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
